### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### Create Document (Tenant A)
POST http://localhost:8080/documents
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-a

{
  "id": "doc-1",
  "title": "Introduction to Distributed Systems",
  "content": "A distributed system is a system whose components are located on different networked computers, which communicate and coordinate their actions by passing messages to one another."
}

### Create Document (Tenant B)
POST http://localhost:8080/documents
Content-Type: application/json
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-b

{
  "id": "doc-2",
  "title": "Vector Databases in RAG",
  "content": "Vector databases are optimized for storing and querying high-dimensional vectors, making them ideal for Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) workflows."
}

### Search Documents (Tenant A - Should find Distributed Systems)
GET http://localhost:8080/search?q=distributed
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-a

### Search Documents (Tenant B - Should find Vector Databases)
GET http://localhost:8080/search?q=vector
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-b

### Cross-Tenant Search Check (Tenant A - Should NOT find Vector Databases)
GET http://localhost:8080/search?q=vector
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-a

### Get Document Details
GET http://localhost:8080/documents/doc-1
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-a

### Delete Document
DELETE http://localhost:8080/documents/doc-1
X-Tenant-Id: tenant-a
